  transcript: "Emotional intelligence involves recognising and managing one’s own emotions while understanding the feelings of others. It plays a key role in communication, teamwork, and leadership. People with strong emotional intelligence can handle conflict more effectively and build better relationships. Many workplaces now include emotional intelligence training to improve collaboration.",
